msgid ""
"I cannot see my house on the map / Why should I use &marble; if there is "
"<application>Google Earth</application> already?"
msgstr ""
"Ne mogu pronaći svoju kuću a mapi/ Zašto koristiti &marble; iako postoji "
"Google Earth?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1209
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&marble; aims to be a lightweight fast educational geographical browser that "
"easily runs on any platform that is supported by &Qt;. While higher "
"resolution maps would be nice to have they aren't necessary for every user "
"and every use case (just like you don't use a full blown text processor each "
"time you just need a simple editor). Also notice &marble; is free software "
"and is based on data that can be freely redistributed in the same way that "
"applies to Free Software."
msgstr ""
"&marble; ima za cilj da bude lagan i brz obrazovni geografski browser koji "
"lako radi na bilo kojoj platformi koju podržava &Qt;. Dok bi za veće mape "
"trebalo imati veću rezoluciju, ipak nije neophodno za svakog korisnika i "
"svaku upotrebu (kada ne koristite veliki opseg teksta procesor treba samo "
"jednostavan editor). Također primijetite da je &marble;  slobodni softver, a "
"zasniva se na podacima koji se mogu slobodno redistribuirati na isti način "
"na koji se odnosi i na slobodni softver."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why is &marble; so fast although I don't have hardware acceleration "
"enabled? / Why doesn't &marble; run smoothly on my expensive 3D graphics "
"card?"
msgstr ""
"Zašto je &marble; tako brz uprkos tomu što nemam omogućeno hardversko "
"ubrzanje) Zašto se &marble; ne pokreće tako lahko na mojoj skupoj 3D "
"grafičkoj kartici?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Despite depicting the earth as a globe &marble; doesn't make use of any 3D "
"hardware acceleration. This has the advantage of running at a decent speed "
"on any platform and hardware supported by &Qt;. However it has the "
"disadvantage that it doesn't run as smoothly as it could if it used hardware "
"accelerated OpenGL. &marble; just uses plain 2D graphics and therefore "
"requires a graphics adapter that is fast at drawing 2D graphics. We plan to "
"add an optional OpenGL backend in the future."
msgstr ""
"Uprkos prikazu Zemlje kao kugle &marble; ne koristi bilo koju 3D hardversku "
"akceleraciju. To ima prednost jer radi na pristojnim brzinama na bilo kojoj "
"platformi i hardveru, također podržava &Qt;. Međutim, ima manu da ne radi "
"onako lahko kao što bi mogao, ako se koristi hardverska akceleraciju OpenGL. "
"&marble; Koristi samo običanu 2D grafiku i stoga zahtijeva za grafičku "
"karticu koja izvršava brzo crtanje 2D grafike. Planiramo dodati opcionalni "
"OpenGL backend u budućnosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1224
#, no-c-format
msgid "Will I ever have to pay for &marble;?"
msgstr "Da li će se ikada morati plaćati &marble; ?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1227
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "No, never. But the authors always welcome feedback. &marble; is licensed "
#| "under the <ulink url=\"http://www.gnu.org/licenses/licenses.html#LGPL"
#| "\">LGPL</ulink>, so you will never have to pay for this program."
msgid ""
"No, never. But the authors always welcome feedback. &marble; is licensed "
"under the <ulink url=\"https://www.gnu.org/licenses/licenses.html#LGPL"
"\">LGPL</ulink>, so you will never have to pay for this program."
msgstr ""
"Ne, nikada. Autorima su uvijek poželjne povratne informacije. &marble; "
"licencu možete pogledati na <ulink url=\"http://www.gnu.org/licenses/"
"licenses.html#LGPL\">LGPL</ulink>, tako da nikada nećete morati plaćati za "
"ovaj program."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1233
#, no-c-format
msgid "How can I contribute?"
